properties.doc: If set to true, then router will match workers to jobs even if they don't match label selectors. Warning: You may get workers that are not qualified for a job they are matched with if you set this variable to true. This flag is intended more for temporary usage. By default, set to false.

properties.doc: Define a scoring rule to use, when calculating a score to determine the best worker. If not set, will use a default scoring formula that uses the number of job labels that the worker labels match, as well as the number of label selectors the worker labels match and/or exceed using a logistic function (https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Logistic_function).

type.doc:
A rule of one of the following types:
StaticRule:  A rule providing static rules that always return the same result, regardless of input.
DirectMapRule:  A rule that return the same labels as the input labels.
ExpressionRule: A rule providing inline expression rules.
FunctionRule: A rule providing a binding to an HTTP Triggered Azure Function.
WebhookRule: A rule providing a binding to a webserver following OAuth2.0 authentication protocol.

properties.doc: A set of key/value pairs that are identifying attributes used by the rules engines to make decisions. Values must be primitive values - number, string, boolean.

properties.name: tags
properties.doc: A set of non-identifying attributes attached to this worker. Values must be primitive values - number, string, boolean.

properties.name: channels
properties.doc: Collection of channel(s) this worker can handle and their impact on the workers capacity.

valueType.name: RouterChannel
valueType.doc: Represents the capacity a job in this channel will consume from a worker.

properties.name: channelId
properties.doc: Id of a channel.

properties.name: capacityCostPerJob
properties.doc: The amount of capacity that an instance of a job of this channel will consume of the total worker capacity.

properties.name: maxNumberOfJobs
properties.doc: The maximum number of jobs that can be supported concurrently for this channel. Value must be greater than zero.

properties.name: offers
properties.doc: A list of active offers issued to this worker.

valueType.name: RouterJobOffer
valueType.doc: An offer of a job to a worker.

properties.name: offerId
properties.doc: Id of an offer.

properties.name: jobId
properties.doc: Id of the job.

properties.name: capacityCost
properties.doc: The capacity cost consumed by the job offer.

properties.name: offeredAt
properties.doc: Timestamp when the offer was created in UTC.

properties.name: expiresAt
properties.doc: Timestamp when the offer will expire in UTC.

properties.name: assignedJobs
properties.doc: A list of assigned jobs attached to this worker.

valueType.name: RouterWorkerAssignment
valueType.doc: The assignment for a worker to a job.

properties.name: assignmentId
properties.doc: Id of the assignment.

properties.name: jobId
properties.doc: Id of the job assigned.

properties.name: capacityCost
properties.doc: The amount of capacity this assignment has consumed on the worker.

properties.name: assignedAt
properties.doc: The assignment time of the job in UTC.

properties.name: loadRatio
properties.doc: A value indicating the workers capacity. A value of '1' means all capacity is consumed. A value of '0' means no capacity is currently consumed.

properties.name: availableForOffers
properties.doc: A flag indicating this worker is open to receive offers or not.

properties.name: maxConcurrentOffers
properties.doc: If this is set, the worker will only receive up to this many new offers at a time.
